    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="552"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d552">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <gloss target="#t_Generalissimo1">Generalissimo</gloss>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CKS1" type="from">Chiang</persName> to President
                            <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d552fn1">Sent via Army channels from <persName
                            corresp="#p_HTG1">Hearn</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_MGC1"
                            >Marshall</persName>, “eyes only”, for delivery to <persName
                            corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName>.</note>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-03">3 February
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>I appreciate your desire to open the Ledo Road, a desire which is also my great
                    concern since it is only thru the opening of this land route that China may
                    quickly obtain the heavy equipment much needed by her Army. You doubtless recall
                    that at Cairo I reiterated and emphasized the fact that I am ready to send the
                    Yunnan troops into Burma at any moment that large scale amphibious landing
                    operations can be effected at strategic points.<note n="2" xml:id="d552fn2">See
                            <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_347">pp. 347</ref>–<ref
                            target="#pg_350">350</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I stand ready to adhere to this decision, and hope that we can carry out
                    operations even before November of this year, which date you mentioned as
                    possible and probable for the diverting of the amphibious equipment to
                    Burma.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
